  "body": "I am testing out React and I have discovered some inconsistencies between all other browsers and Safari 8.0.3 on OS X. When I try to call the this.getDOMNode() from within Safari 8.0.3 the DOM node returned is not the actual node that is mounted in the DOM, I suspect it is the virtual copy from reacts virtual DOM. I try to call getBoundingClientRect() on it, and it returns an empty ClientRect object.\nThe same code works as expected in Chrome (Version 39.0.2171.95 64-bit) and Firefox (35.0.1)\n\nWorth noting, I am using the jsx preprocessor reactify with gulp.\n\n``` javascript\nvar React = require('react');\nmodule.exports = React.createClass({\n    componentDidMount : function() {\n        var node = this.getDOMNode();\n        console.log(node);\n        var rect = node.getBoundingClientRect();\n        console.log(rect);\n    },\n    render : function() {\n        return (\n            <div className=\"react-error\" >\n            </div>\n        );\n    }\n});\n```\n",
